Basal segment of chelicera relatively large, with slightly concave ventral margin; chela small crescent-shaped (
Fig. 5
). Pedipalp short (
Fig. 6
): P-1 very short, without setae; P-2 with single dorsal seta near middle of segment; P-3 with very long, thick proximal seta and comparatively short, fine dorsodistal one; P-4 with two thin proximal setae, one thick, spine-like seta and massive dorsodistal claw; P-5 small with one solenidion, and seven simple setae: one very long, thick seta, three setae moderately long, thick, one curved pectinate seta and two short setae (thick and thin).
